  "author" : "rl.starbound",
  "description" : "Better Crew & NPC Behavior improves NPC behavior logic, with special focus on crew members. In the base game, the crew tend to clump around the ship's teleporter because that is their \"home\" location. This mod dynamically and randomly sets crew \"home\" locations to objects on the ship that are related to each crew member's role, resulting in a crew that moves about a well decorated ship more naturally.\n\nIn addition, improvements have been made to NPC combat, and a large number of bugs in general NPC behavior have been fixed, resulting in behavior that appears to be more realistic.\n\nFind documentation and the source code at:\nhttps://github.com/rl-starbound/rl_bettercrew",
  "friendlyName" : "Better Crew & NPC Behavior",
  "includes" : ["QuickbarMini", "FrackinUniverse"],
  "name" : "rl_bettercrew",
  "version" : "2.0.0"
}
